                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra (name of St Mary in Texts I-4, I-5);
                           titles and numbers of the Pss. and Canticles; incipits and numbers of
                           Songs; title of Texts I-2, I-3 and I-5; title and incipit of the daily
                           readings of Text I-4; name and traditional interpretation of some of the
                           Hebrew letters in Ps. 118; letters ስ and ሕ in the word ስብሕዎ in Ps. 150;
                           letters ይ, ር and ዎ in the word ይባርክዎ in Canticle 10; doxology at the end
                           of Texts I-2 (fol. 140r) and I-3 (fol. 147v); elements of the punctuation
                           signs and text dividers; elements ofEthiopic numerals.
 
 A few
                           lines (alternating with black lines) on the incipit page of Text I-1 to
                           I-3 and on fol. 158ra; two groups of lines on the incipit page of Texts
                           I-4 and I-5.</seg>
                     </handNote>
