                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1ra">f. 1ra</locus>
                           <desc>b: Excerpt from the mälkǝʾ-hymn to Fanuel (ChRep p. 202, n</desc>
                           <locus target="#166">166</locus>). <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#1ra">1ra</locus>b:  ሰላም፡ ለዝከርረምከ፡ ዘጊ[ይደ]ልዋ፡
                              ተበፅኦ፡...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> ChRep p. 202, n<locus target="#166">166</locus>
                           <note>. The note is written in a mediocre hand (hairlines and strong
                              bifocation of some elements) in black and faded red ink. Partly
                              illegible, possibly written over an older note at the bottom of the
                              fol. The angles Fanuʾel and Mikāʾel are mentioned. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2v">f. 2v</locus>
                           <desc>: Calendaric note containing the feast days.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The ink of the note is almost completely faded, and the text is
                              illegible. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#126r">f. 126r-126</locus>
                           <desc>v: Calendaric note containing the feast days.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#126r">126r</locus>: በስመ፡ በል፡ ሰ፡ ሠረቀ፡ መስከረም፡ ፩፡
                              በ[n.l.]፡ ዮሐንስ፡ በርተ፡ ሎሜዎስ፡ በ፰፡ ዘካርያስ፡ በ፲፡ ጸደንጌ፡ በ፲፭፡ እስጢፋኖስ፡...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in a trained hand, the ink is fading out towards the
                              bottom of the fols. and those parts are illegible. The directive በስመ፡
                              በል፡ “Recite the Trinitarian formula” is in Amharic, the rest of the
                              note is written in Gǝʿǝz. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#162vb">f. 162vb</locus>
                           <desc>: Ownership note. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#162vb">162vb</locus>:  ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘዳዊት፡ &lt;…&gt; ወለውሉ፡
                              ይኩኖሙ፡ ለመድኃኒተ፡ ሥጋ፡ ወነፍስ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። ዱ፡ ሳሙኤል፡ መልከ፡ ጼዴቅ፡ ወለተ፡
                              ሀና።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note consists of two parts, written in red and black ink by
                              two different scribes. The original note was partly erased and
                              complemented with additional text, given here in brackets. According
                              to the note, the book belongs to Dāwit and his children Sāmuʾel, Mälkä
                              Ṣedeq and Walatta Hana. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#163ra">f. 163ra-164</locus>
                           <desc>ra: ʾƎsaggǝd laki ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām... “I worship Thee, my Lady
                              Mary…” (ChRep p. 318, n</desc>
                           <locus target="#336">336</locus>).<quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#163ra">163ra</locus>: እሰግድ፡ ለኪ፡ እግዝእትየ፡ ማርያም፡ ለፀሐየ፡
                              {ጽድቅ፡} ሠረገላሁ። ለመርዓዌ፡ ሰማይ፡ ጽርሑ።…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> ChRep p. 318, n<locus target="#336">336</locus>
                           <note>. The note is written in a mediocre hand, in red and black (letters
                              with strong hairlines, especially for the letter ግ). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#164rb">f. 164rb</locus>
                           <desc>-va: Prayer to St Mary from Säʿatat.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#164rb">164rb</locus>: ኵሎሙ፡ ሠራዊተ፡ መላእክት፡ ይሴብሑኪ፡ ዘእምቅድመ፡
                              ዓለም፡ ሀልዎተኪ፡ ለማኀደረ፡ ወልዱ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ኃረየኪ።…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in a mediocre hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The Pss. are divided into groups of ten separated by
                           chains of red and black dots.
 - The midpoint of the “Psalms of
                           David” (in P<locus target="#77">77</locus>) is marked on <locus target="#65v">65v</locus> (see also “Decorations”).
 - The scribe
                           reduced the size of his handwriting, used compressed script or wrote in
                           between lines to accommodate the end of a Ps.: e.g., fols.7r, 10v, 60r,
                           103v.
 - Some lines of Pss. are written over erasures: e.g., <locus target="#5v">5v</locus>, 6r, the entire <locus target="#86r">86r</locus> was erased and rewritten. 
 - Spaces for rubrication
                           are left unfilled on <locus target="#151v">151v</locus>, 152r.
 -
                           Notes written in the upper margins or in between lines in the same hand:
                              <locus target="#143v">143v</locus>, 144v, 145v.
 - Writing
                           exercises and crude doodles: <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>, 2r, 164v,
                           165r.
 - Erased note: <locus target="#165ra">165ra</locus>.
 -
                           Notes in a secondary hand and faded red ink (partly illegible) are
                           written throughout the Ms., e.g. <locus target="#25v">25v</locus>, 27v,
                           29r, 32v.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- A red thread inserted in the upper corner of fols.
                              140, 147.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
